# Chokmah Mobile Environment Variables

# API URL Configuration
# Uncomment and set the appropriate URL for your backend
# This is optional - you can also change the environment in src/constants/api.js

# For local development:
# API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# For production:
# API_URL=https://chokmah-resources-backend.onrender.com

# For custom URL:
# API_URL=http://your-custom-url.com

# ============================================
# Android Emulator Note:
# ============================================
# Android emulator cannot access 'localhost' on your machine.
# Use one of these instead:
#   - 10.0.2.2:3000 (Android emulator's special alias for host machine)
#   - Your computer's IP address (e.g., 192.168.1.100:3000)
#
# The app automatically handles this for you when using the default
# configuration in src/constants/api.js

# ============================================
# Physical Device Testing:
# ============================================
# If testing on a physical device, you must use your computer's
# IP address on the local network:
#   API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3000
#
# To find your IP:
#   - Mac/Linux: ifconfig | grep "inet "
#   - Windows: ipconfig
#   - Look for your local network IP (usually starts with 192.168 or 10.0)

# ============================================
# How to Use:
# ============================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Uncomment and set your API_URL
#
# 3. Restart your app to pick up changes
